sequenceDiagram
    actor "User / System Load" as UserSystemLoad
    participant "EMP Backend API" as EMPBackendAPI
    participant "Prometheus" as Prometheus
    participant "Alertmanager" as Alertmanager
    participant "Notification Channel" as NotificationChannel
    participant "On-Call Engineer" as OnCallEngineer

    activate EMPBackendAPI
    UserSystemLoad->>EMPBackendAPI: 1. 1. [Cause] Increased traffic/load is applied to the API
    EMPBackendAPI-->>UserSystemLoad: HTTP 2xx (with high latency)
    EMPBackendAPI->>EMPBackendAPI: 2. 2. [Internal] Record high request duration via OpenTelemetry instrumentation
    Prometheus->>EMPBackendAPI: 3. 3. [Scrape] Periodically pull metrics
    EMPBackendAPI-->>Prometheus: 200 OK with Prometheus exposition format text
    activate Prometheus
    Prometheus->>Prometheus: 4. 4. [Evaluate] Continuously evaluate configured alert rule against time-series data
    activate Alertmanager
    Prometheus->>Alertmanager: 5. 5. [Fire] Send alert when rule condition is met for its 'FOR' duration
    Alertmanager->>Alertmanager: 6. 6. [Process] Deduplicate, group, and route alert based on configured policies
    activate NotificationChannel
    Alertmanager->>NotificationChannel: 7. 7. [Notify] Send formatted notification to configured receiver
    NotificationChannel->>OnCallEngineer: 8. 8. [Outcome] On-call engineer receives an alert notification

    note over Prometheus: The 'FOR: 5m' clause in the Prometheus alert rule is critical to prevent 'flapping' alerts from t...
    note over Alertmanager: Alertmanager's grouping logic is key to reducing alert fatigue. For instance, if 10 API pods are ...
    note over EMPBackendAPI: The /metrics endpoint is a pull-based model. It must be designed to be highly performant and ligh...

    deactivate NotificationChannel
    deactivate Alertmanager
    deactivate Prometheus
    deactivate EMPBackendAPI
